# 🧱 STEP 1 — FIX NODE LABEL RENDERING (CRITICAL)

Replace incorrect rendering:

❌ “[object Object]”

---

## IMPLEMENT

```js
label: {
  formatter: params => {
    return params.data.label || params.data.name;
  }
}
```

---

# 🧱 STEP 2 — SWITCH TO CARD-STYLE NODES

Replace pill UI with structured card layout.

---

## IMPLEMENT

```js
label: {
  backgroundColor: "#ffffff",
  borderColor: "#E5E7EB",
  borderWidth: 1,
  borderRadius: 8,
  padding: [8, 12],
  color: "#111827",
  fontSize: 12,
  lineHeight: 18
}
```

---

## FORMAT CONTENT

```js
formatter: params => {
  const name = params.data.name;
  const role = params.data.role || "";
  return `${name}\n${role}`;
}
```

---

# 🧱 STEP 3 — HIERARCHY-BASED STYLING

Apply visual differentiation by depth.

---

## IMPLEMENT

```js
label: {
  formatter: params => {
    const depth = params.treePathInfo.length - 1;

    if (depth === 0) return `{root|${params.name}}`;
    if (depth === 1) return `{manager|${params.name}}`;
    return `{employee|${params.name}}`;
  },
  rich: {
    root: { fontSize: 16, fontWeight: "bold" },
    manager: { fontSize: 13 },
    employee: { fontSize: 11 }
  }
}
```

---

# 🧱 STEP 4 — FIX LAYOUT & SPACING

Ensure readability and prevent overlap.

---

## IMPLEMENT

```js
layout: "orthogonal",
orient: "vertical",
nodeGap: 30,
layerGap: 80
```

---

# 🧱 STEP 5 — ENABLE EXPAND / COLLAPSE

Show only top levels initially.

---

## IMPLEMENT

```js
initialTreeDepth: 2
```

